content:
There's a problem in the CI-build version of carin-bb:

this page: https://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/carin-bb/ValueSet-CARIN-BB-DiagnosisType.html refers to http://hl7.org/fhir/us/carin/ValueSet/carin-bb-diagnosistype which is not valid.

This appears to be problem in the canonical URL?
Thanks @Grahame Grieve. @Amol Vyas is going to take a look.

Grahame Grieve said:

There's a problem in the CI-build version of carin-bb:

this page: https://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/carin-bb/ValueSet-CARIN-BB-DiagnosisType.html refers to http://hl7.org/fhir/us/carin/ValueSet/carin-bb-diagnosistype which is not valid.

This appears to be problem in the canonical URL?

Hi @Grahame Grieve , thanks for letting us know. Could you please give more details?
Does this problem exist on other Value Set pages as well? For example: https://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/carin-bb/ValueSet-CARIN-BB-Identifier-Type.html referring to http://hl7.org/fhir/us/carin/ValueSet/carin-bb-identifier-type?

I believe the IG hasn't been updated since the Feb2020 ballot, so trying to see if this is an old, pre-ballot problem or something that surfaced during a recent (March 16 from qa.html ) build perhaps using a newer version of IGPublisher. @Saul Kravitz
that one is not correct either. the canonical URL must be http://hl7.org/fhir/us/carin-bb/ValueSet/carin-bb-identifier-type

Grahame Grieve said:

that one is not correct either. the canonical URL must be http://hl7.org/fhir/us/carin-bb/ValueSet/carin-bb-identifier-type

Thank you. We will work on fixing those (and any other) canonical urls with the correct id ("carin-bb"). @Mark Roberts @Pat Taylor @Dave Hill
I suspect these issues will sort out when we have a new CI build from FSH sources.
